### Test OTP Registration Flow
### Step 1: Register a new account (generates OTP)

POST http://localhost:8000/api/accounts/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "Test",
    "lastName": "OTPUser",
    "email": "testotp9999@example.com",
    "password": "TestPass123!",
    "confirmPassword": "TestPass123!",
    "contactNum": "09171234567",
    "birthDate": "1995-05-15",
    "street_address": "123 Test Street",
    "city": "Zamboanga City",
    "province": "Zamboanga del Sur",
    "postal_code": "7000",
    "country": "Philippines"
}

### Step 2: Verify OTP (replace OTP_CODE with value from registration response)
### The field name is "otp" NOT "otp_code"

POST http://localhost:8000/api/accounts/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testotp9999@example.com",
    "otp": "REPLACE_WITH_OTP"
}

### Step 3: Login after verification

POST http://localhost:8000/api/accounts/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testotp9999@example.com",
    "password": "TestPass123!"
}

### Step 4: Resend OTP (if needed) - 60 second cooldown

POST http://localhost:8000/api/accounts/resend-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testotp9999@example.com"
}
